 line options. The output of `epijats --help` is:\n\n```\nusage: __main__.py [-h] [--from {jats,json,jsoml,html}]\n                   [--to {json,jsoml,html,html+pdf,pdf}] [--no-web-fonts]\n                   inpath outpath\n\nEprint JATS\n\npositional arguments:\n  inpath                input directory/path\n  outpath               output directory/path\n\noptions:\n  -h, --help            show this help message and exit\n  --from {jats,json,jsoml,html}\n                        format of source\n  --to {json,jsoml,html,html+pdf,pdf}\n                        format of target\n  --no-web-fonts        Do not use online web fonts\n```\n\n\nInstallation\n------------\n\n```\npython3 -m pip install epijats[format1,format2,...]\n```\nwhere each `formatN` etc.. is one of `jats`, `html`, `pdf`, or `jsoml`.\nJson support is automatic.\n\n\n### Non-Python requirements\n\nIf you are converting from JATS, the following dependencies must be installed:\n\n<ul>\n  <li> <a href=\"https://pandoc.org\">pandoc</a>\n  <li> pandoc-katex-filter Node.js NPM package\n  <li> git\n</ul>\n\nAll other dependencies will be automatically installed by `pip`.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "epijats.jinja", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "epijats.jinja.style_template_loader", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "jinja2.BaseLoader", "xref": {"fqname": "jinja2.BaseLoader", "project": "jinja2"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "epijats.jinja.WebPageGenerator", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "epijats.jinja.WebPageGenerator.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "epijats.jinja.WebPageGenerator.add_template_loader", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "loader", "type": {"name": "jinja